full_text:
LOOK: Campus publications from across Cebu converged at the University of the Philippines Cebu (UPC) Arts and Sciences (AS) Hall for “PAGSIDLAK: Gilded Resilience through 50 Years of Critical and Fearless Journalism,” held on Saturday, March 16.

The event covered essential aspects of journalism, including fact-checking, news writing, feature writing, photojournalism
, editorial writing, and cartooning.

It was led by acclaimed journalists including Explained PH Founder and Editor-in-Chief
(EIC) Archie Bergosa, new.abs-cbn.com correspondent Victor Kintanar, Rappler Cebu correspondent and Visayas Reporter John Sitchon, former Tug-ani EIC (2022-2023) Clive Joshua Rabuya, Training and Development Head at Explained PH Prences Jhewen Albis, and Chief Cartoonist at Explained PH Maurice Isabelle Gimena.

The journalism workshop was organized by Tug-ani, the official student publication of the UPC.

via Ejay Villaver | FORWARD Staff Writer

full_text:
LOOK: Approximately 65 children participated in the University of San Jose-Recoletos Center for Recollect Community Engagement and Social Involvement’s (USJ-R CRCESI) Paglaum Sa Mga Bata sa Carbon: Health and Wellness II session at the Main Lobby on Saturday, March 16.

The children in attendance were educated on basic hygiene practices in collaboration with third-year Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) students.

Meanwhile, University President Rev. Fr. Eduardo Celiz Jr., OAR blessed the mobile bath stations set up at the Main Quadrangle, which could also be utilized to help nearby communities affected by natural disasters.

Further, a feeding program spearheaded by the Safety and Security Department (SSD) will be conducted around noontime to culminate the activity.

via Rey Martin Rio | FORWARD Staff Writer

full_text:
Eyes here, Josenians!

As we celebrate the Feast Day of St. Joseph, the Office of the President has released a set of activities for the celebration of the said event.

In accordance with a memorandum released on Thursday, March 14, a Holy Mass will be conducted in honor of the solemnity of our patron saint at the Recoletos Coliseum which will be attended by students and employees of the Basak Campus on March 18, Monday at 8 a.m.

In observance of this, the classes of the School of Education (SED) and the School of Computer Studies (SCS) are suspended from 8 a.m. and will resume at 9:30 a.m.

In the USJ-R Main Campus, on the same day, a Holy Mass will be held at the Main Lobby at 3:30 p.m. which suspends the classes starting at 3:15 p.m. and must resume right after the mass has ended.

On the other hand, this March 19, Tuesday, a fiesta celebration in honor of St. Joseph will be attended by the employees from both campuses at the USJ-R Main Lobby from 8 a.m. to 12 p.m.

Please be guided.Eyes here, Josenians!

full_text:
It’s election season in USJ-R!

The USJ-R Commission on Elections issued Resolution No. 03 Series of 2024 — the Calendar of Activities for the 43rd SSC Congress Election.

These are the following schedules:

March 25-26, 2024 – Political Party Registration
April 08-11, 2024 – Filing of Certificate of Candidacy
April 12-13, 2024 – Screening of Candidates
April 15, 2024 – Posting of Tentative List of Candidates
April 16-17, 2024 – Protest Period
April 18-19, 2024 – Replacement Period
April 20 & 22, 2024 – Final Screening of Candidates
April 22, 2024 – Posting of the Official List of Candidates
April 24-26, 2024 – Approval of Election Paraphernalia and Registration of the Speaker’s Bureau
April 29-May 04, 2024 – Campaign Period
May 06, 2024 – Grand Rally, Town Hall and Presidential Debate
May 07, 2024 – Silent Days
May 08, 2024 – Election Day
May 10, 2024 – Inauguration Day

TAKE NOTE: The dates stipulated herein can be changed or amended if the circumstance warrants it. Any amendments to the schedule shall be posted accordingly for everyone's guidance.

For inquiries and clarifications,
contact us through our official email account:
joseniancomelec
.official@gmail
.com
